Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Halve, peel and chop the @Echalion shallot{1} into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Boil your kettle, then pour the @boiled water{500%ml} into a #measuring jug{} with the @vegetable stock paste{20%g}. Stir well and set aside - this is your veg stock.

Heat a drizzle of oil in an #ovenproof pan{} on medium-high heat.

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal pan and transfer to an ovenproof dish before baking.

Once hot, fry the @British smoked bacon lardons{180%g} and shallot until golden, ~{3-4%minutes}. Stir in the garlic and @tomato puree{30%g} and cook for ~{1%minute} more. Add the @risotto rice{175%g}, then stir and cook until the edges of the rice are translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Pour your veg stock into the rice and stir well to combine. Add the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}(halved) and bring back to the boil.

Pop a lid on the pan (or cover with foil) and bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the rice is cooked and the stock has been absorbed, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, grate the @mature Cheddar cheese{60%g}.

While the risotto bakes, halve the @lemon{1/2} and squeeze the lemon juice into a large #bowl{}.

Add the @sugar{1} and @olive oil{1} to the bowl and mix together. Set aside.

When the risotto is ready, remove it from the oven and mix in the @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g}, grated Cheddar, @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} and a knob of @?butter{1%knob} (if you have any).

> TIP: Add a splash of water to loosen the risotto if needed.

Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Add the @pea shoots{40%g} to the bowl of dressing and toss to coat.

Share the risotto between your plates or bowls and serve with the salad alongside. Enjoy!